1
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:15,920
[The construction site of Rongcheng Group]

2
00:00:20,190 --> 00:00:21,020
Gai,

3
00:00:21,510 --> 00:00:23,370
what did you do to offend the boss?

4
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,290
Who said I offended the boss?

5
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:29,830
Then why did you get sent to
the front line?

6
00:00:29,830 --> 00:00:30,390
Yeah.

7
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:34,570
"Front line" is a good way to put it.

8
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:36,320
They even matched you

9
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:38,450
with a job that suits your profession.

10
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:40,130
Come on.

11
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:41,710
Even if I explain it to you,

12
00:00:41,710 --> 00:00:42,660
it's pointless.

13
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:43,740
Let me tell you,

14
00:00:44,070 --> 00:00:45,160
not everyone

15
00:00:45,220 --> 00:00:45,920
can understand

16
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,110
the boss's good intentions.

17
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:47,670
You know?

18
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:49,090
Is it this truck?

19
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:50,150
Yes, yes, this one.

20
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:52,390
Do I have to open the door myself?

21
00:00:52,390 --> 00:00:53,070
Coming.

22
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:55,350
Gai, please.

23
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:57,960
Watch out, Gai.

24
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,760
You're rusty.

25
00:00:58,790 --> 00:00:59,350
Indeed.

26
00:00:59,350 --> 00:00:59,960
Gai, take care.

27
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:00,560
Put it here.

28
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:01,280
Here.

29
00:01:04,310 --> 00:01:04,790
Okay.

30
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,280
Listen,

31
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,840
don't say I didn't warn you.

32
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:10,700
You guys,

33
00:01:11,230 --> 00:01:12,360
if you take care of me properly

34
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,710
during this period,

35
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:14,510
this is a crucial chance

36
00:01:14,510 --> 00:01:16,039
that could change your future.

37
00:01:16,039 --> 00:01:16,510
Got it?

38
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:17,950
We must serve Gai well.

39
00:01:17,950 --> 00:01:18,350
Yes.

40
00:01:18,350 --> 00:01:19,280
We'll definitely take good care of you.

41
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,740
Everyone, pay attention.

42
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:21,789
Recently, someone has been

43
00:01:21,789 --> 00:01:23,039
scattering nails on the road again.

44
00:01:23,039 --> 00:01:23,789
Be careful when driving.

45
00:01:23,789 --> 00:01:25,120
Come, let me take a look.

46
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:27,590
The tires are punctured.

47
00:01:27,590 --> 00:01:28,720
It's too dangerous.

48
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:29,400
My god,

49
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,900
how wicked.

50
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,340
Pay attention.

51
00:01:32,590 --> 00:01:33,450
Pay attention.

52
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:34,780
Go.

53
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:35,430
Rest assured, Gai.

54
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,280
All right, get to work.

55
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:36,940
Get to work.

56
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:09,290
[Born with Luck]

57
00:03:09,380 --> 00:03:12,310
[Episode 10]

58
00:03:32,630 --> 00:03:33,750
If Zheng Yongbing is

59
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,610
really the man we're looking for,

60
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,360
he is upstairs right now

61
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,560
doing who knows what.

62
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,520
And we can only sit in the car,

63
00:03:40,910 --> 00:03:43,240
staring out the window feeling helpless.

64
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:50,579
How about I go up
and take a look right now?

65
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,370
You can't go alone.

66
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:54,079
If you're going, we go together.

67
00:03:54,079 --> 00:03:54,750
You keep an eye out here.

68
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:55,950
I can handle it alone.

69
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,579
I'm a veteran cop.

70
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,680
I know what I'm doing.

71
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,310
Besides, for something like this,

72
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:00,840
I can't let

73
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,870
a girl take the risk.

74
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:02,470
Song Xing.

75
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,600
Li Qian,

76
00:04:03,930 --> 00:04:04,860
know your place.

77
00:04:21,430 --> 00:04:22,830
Miss, come out quickly!

78
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,190
-What kind of crappy elevator is this?
-You scared me.

79
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:26,250
It's broken again.

80
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:27,680
Call the property management.

81
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:29,610
Have them come fix it immediately.

82
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,150
There are so many photos—

83
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,160
I don't believe

84
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,560
we can't find a clear one.

85
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:35,310
In his home

86
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,330
it's like a constant feast,

87
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:41,150
with the earth's milk,

88
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,700
the lush green of forests,

89
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,580
and the tears of the ocean.

90
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,070
But,

91
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:51,750
my friend,

92
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,400
don't envy that kind of evil man.

93
00:05:56,510 --> 00:05:57,360
One day,

94
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,480
the earth's milk…

95
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:05,140
The earth's milk…

96
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,330
The earth's…

97
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,120
At his age,

98
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,390
a decline in memory

99
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:18,000
is normal.

100
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:19,630
Milk.

101
00:06:19,630 --> 00:06:20,040
Beer.

102
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:21,830
Beer.

103
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,360
Hello, Chief.

104
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:28,960
Didn't you say Zheng Yongbing
is on a diet?

105
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,750
His breakfast and lunch are so plain.

106
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:31,600
Why did he buy

107
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:32,470
so much meat

108
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:33,640
and beer for dinner?

109
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:37,880
There's someone else in his room.

110
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,010
You and Song Xing stay put.

111
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:41,159
We'll be right there.

112
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:42,090
But Song Xing...

113
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:42,840
Stay put.

114
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:43,680
Understood?

115
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:46,480
Understood.

116
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:56,920
Sorry.

117
00:06:56,950 --> 00:07:00,080
The subscriber you dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

118
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:32,140
Liu!

119
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:33,430
Sit down.

120
00:07:33,909 --> 00:07:34,310
Come.

121
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:41,370
You must be hungry.

122
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:44,170
There aren't any good dishes.

123
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,840
Just have something simple.

124
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,100
Help yourself.

125
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:50,240
Come.

126
00:07:59,070 --> 00:07:59,670
Liu,

127
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:02,360
what exactly did you

128
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,760
come back for this time?

129
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,160
To be honest,

130
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,330
someone specifically

131
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,800
invited me back

132
00:08:09,870 --> 00:08:11,470
to close a big deal this time.

133
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,190
A big deal?

134
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:16,750
What is it?

135
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,360
Bianzhong.

136
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:24,510
A full set of nine.

137
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,340
My goodness.

138
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,360
If you get caught,
that's a death sentence.

139
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,760
And if I don't get caught?

140
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,430
If I don't get caught,

141
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:32,039
I can make 800,000 yuan.

142
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:34,679
Wait, Liu.

143
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:35,960
I mean,

144
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,840
coming back this time

145
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,960
is too risky.

146
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,270
I heard the police

147
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:42,330
have a 50,000  yuan reward out for you.

148
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,770
I really need the money.

149
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:49,670
Otherwise I wouldn't risk my life

150
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:51,020
for 800,000 yuan.

151
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:56,240
This time coming back to Sanjiangkou,

152
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,080
I didn't even dare to
take public transport.

153
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,340
I was afraid someone would recognize me.

154
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,200
You see,

155
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,180
I came back on a coal train.

156
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:06,240
I didn't dare to go to a hotel either.

157
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,870
So I had to come to you.

158
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:09,870
My life

159
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,320
is in your hands, brother.

160
00:09:18,670 --> 00:09:19,710
Don't worry.

161
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,730
It's absolutely safe here.

162
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:24,520
I believe it.

163
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,040
I'm relieved.

164
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,080
When this is over,

165
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:31,270
I'll reward you handsomely.

166
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,080
Don't mention it.

167
00:10:01,670 --> 00:10:02,480
Sorry,

168
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:05,200
the subscriber you dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

169
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,400
Please redial later.

170
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,050
What's going on?

171
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:17,840
Liu,

172
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,990
there's another advantage here.

173
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,880
No one ever comes looking for me.

174
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,810
It's fine.

175
00:10:33,910 --> 00:10:34,970
I'll go take a look.

176
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,520
Who is it?

177
00:11:21,670 --> 00:11:23,270
Excuse me, Mr. Zheng.

178
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:25,550
The downstairs tenant reported

179
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:27,150
that there's a leak in their apartment.

180
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:27,910
They suspect it's a problem

181
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,130
with your bathroom,

182
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:30,500
so I came to check.

183
00:11:35,390 --> 00:11:36,300
Okay.

184
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,600
I'll go to the bathroom now

185
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,760
and check it out!

186
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:43,360
Come in.

187
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,240
It's the property management.

188
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,640
I don't really know them.

189
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,400
How about I go down and take a look?

190
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,000
What if it's really leaking?

191
00:12:02,270 --> 00:12:02,670
Okay.

192
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,080
You go.

193
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,210
The bathroom is indeed leaking.

194
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,790
Is the leaking water

195
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:13,350
blue?

196
00:12:15,550 --> 00:12:17,440
It seems a bit blue.

197
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,180
Sorry.

198
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,150
We will report it for repair right away.

199
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:27,080
And you are?

200
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,710
I... I am his friend.

201
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:33,640
Why don't you

202
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:35,460
call Mr. Zheng out,

203
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:37,840
and we can go downstairs together
to take a look?

204
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,440
He's inside turning off the water valve.

205
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,700
It's dripping inside.

206
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,650
Otherwise,

207
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,750
you can come in and take a look first.

208
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:46,660
Please come in.

209
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:47,630
After you.

210
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:50,260
Come on.

211
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,960
Let's check the bathroom first.

212
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,260
It's right over there.

213
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,370
Can I ask you a question?

214
00:13:26,390 --> 00:13:28,060
Let's fix the leak first

215
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:29,930
and check the bathroom.

216
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:31,690
Don't be in a hurry.

217
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,870
After you answer my question,

218
00:13:33,870 --> 00:13:35,330
I'll go wherever you want.

219
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:39,360
Speak.

220
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,330
Mr. Zheng,

221
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,980
he wasn't in the bathroom, was he?

222
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:48,960
He was lying in that room.

223
00:14:00,630 --> 00:14:02,300
If I hadn't been taking a shower,

224
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:04,300
I would have been killed by you guys.

225
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:14,000
You were so eager for me
to go to the bathroom,

226
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,860
you must have had bad intentions.

227
00:15:12,990 --> 00:15:20,410
[First Inpatient Department]

228
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,010
[Incoming Call: Mentor]

229
00:15:36,430 --> 00:15:37,970
The department plans
to make an exception and promote her.

230
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:39,440
She needs a year of training.

231
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,840
Keep an eye on her.

232
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:42,600
Don't let anything happen to her.

233
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,680
Your phone is ringing.

234
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:43,690
[Incoming Call: Mentor]

235
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,270
Wait, your phone is ringing.

236
00:15:46,270 --> 00:15:46,980
I know.

237
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:47,920
G- Go quickly.

238
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:51,770
Chief Qi,

239
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:52,960
how is the situation?

240
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:54,120
The suspect Zheng Yongbing

241
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,340
took a hit to the head.

242
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:57,000
It shouldn't be a serious issue.

243
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:57,550
I didn't ask about him.

244
00:15:57,550 --> 00:15:58,350
How is Li Qian?

245
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:05,000
Come with me.

246
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:08,300
[Incoming Call: Mentor]

247
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,600
Chief Zhang, your phone is ringing again.

248
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,270
I know.

249
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:10,510
Who is it?

250
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:13,730
Answer it.

251
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:24,000
It's just a superficial cut—

252
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:24,860
four stitches.

253
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,410
Then why is she still in a coma?

254
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:31,750
Her blood pressure, heart rate, breathing—

255
00:16:31,750 --> 00:16:32,630
everything

256
00:16:32,670 --> 00:16:34,330
came back normal on the tests.

257
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:35,990
[Incoming Call: Mentor]

258
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:37,920
What exactly is going on?

259
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:38,870
When we first came,

260
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:39,840
she was fine.

261
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:41,440
With such a big incident,

262
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,360
I guess she's afraid of being criticized,

263
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,420
so she's faking it.

264
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:49,010
It's like this.

265
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,620
If it's a real coma,

266
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:52,190
the eyeballs won't move.

267
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,080
If it's fake,

268
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:54,480
when exposed to light,

269
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,680
the eyeballs will definitely avoid it.

270
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,790
Please pry her eyelids open.

271
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:12,380
No need,

272
00:17:12,589 --> 00:17:14,720
you can just shine the light directly.

273
00:17:39,510 --> 00:17:40,310
Hello, Mentor.

274
00:17:40,310 --> 00:17:41,110
Zhang Yi'ang,

275
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:42,480
what's going on?

276
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:43,310
Before you left,

277
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:44,550
what did I tell you?

278
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,850
Mentor, you're so well-informed.

279
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:50,010
Say hello to Director Gao.

280
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,790
Mentor, don't worry.

281
00:17:54,790 --> 00:17:55,350
Nothing happened;

282
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:56,240
Li Qian is perfectly fine.

283
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,300
How can I not worry?

284
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:59,000
Hearing that from you

285
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,640
makes me even less reassured.

286
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:01,370
Cut the crap.

287
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:02,160
Start a video call.

288
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,420
I need to see it myself.

289
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:10,430
That's enough.

290
00:18:16,140 --> 00:18:16,810
Mentor,

291
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:18,440
look.

292
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:23,010
[Switch to voice chat]

293
00:18:22,550 --> 00:18:23,820
Why isn't she moving?

294
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,680
You call this "fine"?

295
00:18:28,110 --> 00:18:29,030
I won't pursue

296
00:18:29,030 --> 00:18:31,090
your unauthorized action this time.

297
00:18:31,790 --> 00:18:32,820
Director Gao!

298
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,900
[Switch to voice chat]

299
00:18:33,130 --> 00:18:33,890
Li Qian.

300
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,590
How is it? Are you okay?

301
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:36,650
I'm fine.

302
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:41,310
Has the suspect's identity been found out?

303
00:18:41,310 --> 00:18:42,830
The surveillance footage is too blurry
to make out his face.

304
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,070
We were just about to
conduct an intensive interrogation

305
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:46,510
when Zheng Yongbing
started pretending to be unconscious.

306
00:18:46,510 --> 00:18:48,510
I can tolerate Li Qian faking a coma.

307
00:18:48,510 --> 00:18:50,840
Can I tolerate Zheng Yongbing faking one?

308
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:52,830
Chief Qi,

309
00:18:53,110 --> 00:18:53,960
anyway, Li Qian is fine.

310
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,160
You should go back early.

311
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:55,620
Well...

312
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:57,370
How do you

313
00:18:57,510 --> 00:18:59,570
plan to interrogate Zheng Yongbing?

314
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,460
I have to make him talk.

315
00:19:02,590 --> 00:19:03,650
Calm down.

316
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,720
Make sure you don't break the rules.

317
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,940
As long as the facts exist,

318
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:09,620
the masks will be torn off.

319
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:11,610
Don't worry.

320
00:19:15,830 --> 00:19:17,290
Thanks for your hard work.

321
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:17,650
Okay.

322
00:19:21,070 --> 00:19:22,270
Which room? Let's go.

323
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:28,110
[Inpatient Department]

324
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:36,480
♪ Snow blankets the Volga River ♪

325
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:48,660
Did he move?

326
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:49,290
Yes.

327
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,310
His eyes didn't move on my side.

328
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:52,110
It did on mine.

329
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,660
Peel his eyelids open.

330
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:58,800
Wait, did I go to the wrong room?

331
00:20:00,590 --> 00:20:01,850
What's his condition?

332
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,550
Blunt-force injury with a laceration.

333
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:06,880
He's had four stitches.

334
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,620
Then why is he in a coma too?

335
00:20:09,830 --> 00:20:11,680
His blood pressure, heart rate, breathing—

336
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:12,900
all test results

337
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:14,310
are normal.

338
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:16,310
So we've moved directly

339
00:20:16,310 --> 00:20:17,110
to this stage.

340
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:18,880
For a situation like his,

341
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,740
how can I wake him up immediately?

342
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,170
There are many ways.

343
00:20:22,510 --> 00:20:23,490
But...

344
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,010
Let's talk outside.

345
00:21:03,350 --> 00:21:04,010
Put it away.

346
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:05,550
Sit.

347
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:09,510
Get out of the way.

348
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:11,520
You got nerve.

349
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,400
Who hit you over the head?

350
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:22,930
I don't know.

351
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:23,480
No.

352
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:24,750
I don't know him.

353
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,400
You don't recognize him,
but he goes to your place to eat?

354
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,790
He's... He's just a customer

355
00:21:29,790 --> 00:21:30,760
at the store.

356
00:21:31,030 --> 00:21:32,790
He occasionally asked me out for a drink.

357
00:21:32,790 --> 00:21:33,790
That's how we met.

358
00:21:34,070 --> 00:21:35,110
I call him Liu.

359
00:21:36,310 --> 00:21:36,910
That's...

360
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:38,570
That's all I know.

361
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,090
Liu's his full name?

362
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:41,790
Liu Bei.

363
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,400
Is his courtesy name Xuande?

364
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,460
You better behave!

365
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,680
"Bei" as in "houbei"?

366
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,340
It's "Bei" as in "houbei".

367
00:21:47,750 --> 00:21:48,950
"Bei" as in "beihou".

368
00:21:49,030 --> 00:21:49,480
This

369
00:21:49,590 --> 00:21:50,420
Bei.

370
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:52,910
Is that Liu Bei—

371
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,480
the tomb raider

372
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,610
who scams scammers?

373
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,440
You even know this, Chief Zhang?

374
00:22:01,380 --> 00:22:03,830
He's a fugitive wanted
under a Ministry of Public Security order.

375
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:04,550
The department has been

376
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:06,210
tracking him all these years.

377
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:07,440
A few years ago, this Liu Bei

378
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,690
set up a Ponzi scheme.

379
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,090
Impressive.

380
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,310
He claimed

381
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:12,510
he had already tunneled into

382
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:14,680
the burial chamber
of First Emperor of Qin's mausoleum.

383
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:16,440
Many people lost their life savings

384
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,520
to his scams.

385
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:19,010
Families were ruined.

386
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:20,310
A few people were upset,

387
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:21,030
went looking for him,

388
00:22:21,030 --> 00:22:22,400
and he stabbed two of them to death.

389
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,600
You've got a whole archive in your head.

390
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:25,920
Does... Does this count as

391
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,030
harboring a wanted criminal?

392
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:28,290
It definitely counts.

393
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:29,590
No.

394
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:31,950
I... I didn't want to!

395
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,600
He suddenly came to me.

396
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,110
He's a reckless guy.

397
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,590
How could I refuse?

398
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:38,960
Harboring a wanted criminal is now...

399
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,590
It is punishable by up to
three years in prison,

400
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:41,790
or criminal detention
or public surveillance;

401
00:22:41,790 --> 00:22:43,550
in serious cases, it's three to ten years.

402
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:44,200
No.

403
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:45,230
Officers!

404
00:22:45,830 --> 00:22:47,230
I don't want to go to jail!

405
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:48,440
I know the policy.

406
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:50,680
Ask whatever you want.

407
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:51,880
As long as I know,

408
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:52,920
I'll tell you everything.

409
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,550
I was really threatened by him.

410
00:22:54,550 --> 00:22:55,640
Where is he now?

411
00:22:56,350 --> 00:22:57,080
I don't know.

412
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:58,000
But I know

413
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,400
he arrived by hopping on a coal train.

414
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,790
He took a shower at my place,

415
00:23:00,790 --> 00:23:02,510
leaving black water everywhere.

416
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:04,070
Why did he come to Sanjiangkou?

417
00:23:04,070 --> 00:23:05,030
He said

418
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:07,920
someone wanted to
buy a set of bianzhong from him.

419
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,960
He had the bianzhong.

420
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,640
He was acting as a middleman this time.

421
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,830
He said after it's done,

422
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:13,090
he'd get a commission.

423
00:23:14,110 --> 00:23:16,110
Do you know the transaction amount?

424
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,490
I don't know about that.

425
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,300
Is that all?

426
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:22,900
That's all.

427
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:32,680
But according to our intel,

428
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:36,030
you're involved in more than just this.

429
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:41,780
What else is there?

430
00:23:46,770 --> 00:23:48,100
I'll be honest with you.

431
00:23:49,030 --> 00:23:50,960
That matter has been traced to you.

432
00:23:54,310 --> 00:23:54,880
Otherwise,

433
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:57,410
did you think we invited you
for dinner today?

434
00:23:58,070 --> 00:23:58,960
We didn't come here today

435
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,960
for Liu Bei.

436
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:01,350
He's just a side note.

437
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:02,530
We are here for you.

438
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:06,160
Go on.

439
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:12,640
You speak, or I speak?

440
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:14,930
I'll say it then.

441
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:18,720
I… I did suspect

442
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:21,050
there was something wrong with those two.

443
00:24:23,070 --> 00:24:23,980
Are you done?

444
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:26,040
Tell us the whole process, okay?

445
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:28,440
Not long ago,

446
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,070
two men in their thirties

447
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:33,000
suddenly showed up at my door

448
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,720
and asked if I wanted to buy some stuff.

449
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,380
They gave me some gold jewelry

450
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:38,460
and a fake God of Wealth statue.

451
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:39,830
I suspected at the time

452
00:24:39,830 --> 00:24:41,290
that the stuff was stolen.

453
00:24:41,350 --> 00:24:43,400
But they threatened me with a knife.

454
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:44,410
Officers.

455
00:24:44,590 --> 00:24:46,110
I'm a victim too.

456
00:24:46,270 --> 00:24:47,590
Why are you always getting threatened?

457
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:48,590
Exactly.

458
00:24:48,590 --> 00:24:49,080
I'm just

459
00:24:49,110 --> 00:24:50,000
out of luck.

460
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:50,630
And then?

461
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:52,200
Then,

462
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,550
to cut my losses,

463
00:24:53,550 --> 00:24:54,480
I sold the stuff.

464
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:55,920
To whom?

465
00:24:56,070 --> 00:24:56,680
Zhou Qi,

466
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:58,640
the PR manager of

467
00:24:58,640 --> 00:24:59,970
Fenglinwan Nightclub.

468
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:03,310
And that fake God of Wealth statue—

469
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:04,750
I sold it to Hu Jianren

470
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:06,010
from Rongcheng Group.

471
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:08,080
I got 60,000 yuan for it.

472
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:10,790
What about the people who sold it to you?

473
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:25,120
Find someone immediately.

474
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,550
Based on Zheng Yongbing's description,

475
00:25:26,550 --> 00:25:27,750
get the sketches of these two suspects

476
00:25:27,750 --> 00:25:28,400
done first.

477
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:28,790
Okay.

478
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,460
Where is Song Xing?

479
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:33,120
Chief.

480
00:25:34,790 --> 00:25:35,610
Song Xing.

481
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,680
Li Qian was afraid you'd be in danger,

482
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:38,480
so she went in.

483
00:25:39,030 --> 00:25:39,510
Right?

484
00:25:40,070 --> 00:25:40,550
No.

485
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,350
I didn't want her to take risks,

486
00:25:42,350 --> 00:25:43,550
so I didn't let her go up.

487
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:44,070
But later,

488
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:44,790
I have no idea

489
00:25:44,790 --> 00:25:45,880
why she went up by herself.

490
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:46,590
Talk less.

491
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:51,890
Did you find anything at the scene?

492
00:25:51,920 --> 00:25:52,310
Yes.

493
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:56,400
Chief,

494
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:02,840
this is the suspect's backpack.

495
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:05,540
[Jinshui Pavilion]

496
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,960
There are only a few clothes inside.

497
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:07,030
It's cursive script.

498
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:08,540
Hegegao.

499
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:09,720
Jinshui Pavilion.

500
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:12,120
It should be pronounced Jinshui Pavilion.

501
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:19,980
Jinshui Pavilion.

502
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,540
Song Xing, come here for a second.

503
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:35,850
[Inpatient Department]

504
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:39,130
Look what you've done!

505
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:42,670
What are you laughing at?

506
00:26:42,830 --> 00:26:45,790
[Protect the environment,
safeguard our home.]

507
00:26:50,070 --> 00:26:52,200
Do I have to teach you how to open a door?

508
00:27:03,090 --> 00:27:04,520
No need.

509
00:27:04,550 --> 00:27:05,680
I'll open it for you.

510
00:27:06,270 --> 00:27:07,030
[Protect the environment,
safeguard our home.]

511
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,850
This is exhausting.

512
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:21,430
Sit.

513
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:25,440
Tea?

514
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:28,880
Coffee?

515
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,200
Come, have some snacks.

516
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:34,540
Spit it out.

517
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,040
Kai,

518
00:27:43,030 --> 00:27:45,000
I wasn't joking about

519
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:46,480
what I told you last time.

520
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:47,720
No, no.

521
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,000
Let me finish.

522
00:27:50,030 --> 00:27:51,030
What's the rush?

523
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,550
Have a seat.

524
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:57,530
This matter is extremely important to me.

525
00:27:58,480 --> 00:27:59,240
You know

526
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:00,590
I am someone

527
00:28:00,590 --> 00:28:02,190
who has always been upright.

528
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:03,630
You are just stupid.

529
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,640
You've got such a good position

530
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,680
and you don't even know how to
line your own pockets.

531
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,540
No wonder my sister divorced you.

532
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,740
I guess it's just my personality.

533
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,570
Right now, a bunch of corrupt officials

534
00:28:15,570 --> 00:28:16,520
want to oust me

535
00:28:16,550 --> 00:28:18,400
and transfer me to the provincial capital.

536
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:18,920
Then,

537
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:19,790
they'd use

538
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:21,440
the position of
Director of the Administrative Committee

539
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,900
to line their own pockets.

540
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:23,680
Tell me,

541
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,840
how could I let them succeed?

542
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,500
As for making money,

543
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:28,680
you can work together.

544
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:29,030
No.

545
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:32,170
I absolutely will not do such a thing.

546
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:37,730
The only way I can think of

547
00:28:37,830 --> 00:28:39,640
to stop them right now

548
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,610
is to have you...

549
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:42,160
No.

550
00:28:42,750 --> 00:28:43,480
Please

551
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:44,790
injure me.

552
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,160
If you think

553
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:49,370
I didn't pay you enough last time,

554
00:28:51,030 --> 00:28:51,890
you can take any

555
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:54,090
of the old furniture

556
00:28:54,310 --> 00:28:55,710
and antiques in my house,

557
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:57,090
whatever you want.

558
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,310
I don't collect junk.

559
00:29:00,550 --> 00:29:02,860
My ancestors had some money.

560
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:05,960
These are all genuine

561
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:07,440
antiques.

562
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,270
Slow down.

563
00:29:14,510 --> 00:29:16,270
If this was really made of
yellow rosewood,

564
00:29:16,270 --> 00:29:17,550
then it would indeed be valuable.

565
00:29:17,550 --> 00:29:19,350
But with your cheap firewood...

566
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:21,440
But what if it really is

567
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:22,480
yellow rosewood?

568
00:29:29,510 --> 00:29:31,000
If it really was yellow rosewood,

569
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:31,830
my sister wouldn't have

570
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:33,170
divorced you.

571
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:34,830
Okay.

572
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:36,680
Alright, so these pieces of furniture
aren't worth much—

573
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:38,540
you probably don't care for them.

574
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,070
I am a man of culture.

575
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:42,880
These paintings
and calligraphy on the wall

576
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,680
must be worth something, right?

577
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:45,680
Kai,

578
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:47,870
pick any painting

579
00:29:48,830 --> 00:29:49,690
you like at home

580
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:51,660
and take it.

581
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:56,770
What about this one?

582
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,160
Good eye.

583
00:29:58,880 --> 00:29:59,740
It's by Guo Bin.

584
00:30:01,030 --> 00:30:02,490
Look at this handwriting.

585
00:30:08,110 --> 00:30:09,640
And who is that one by?

586
00:30:12,030 --> 00:30:13,030
By Ding Guanpeng.

587
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:16,270
I also have one by Wen Zhengming.

588
00:30:16,270 --> 00:30:17,470
I'll go get it for you.

589
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:18,440
Wait a minute.

590
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:20,160
Who is this one by?

591
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,740
That one is a fake.

592
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,190
It's a fake, not worth anything.

593
00:30:29,550 --> 00:30:30,290
Let me see.

594
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,070
Yu Yueran?

595
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:38,510
I've heard of this person.

596
00:30:38,510 --> 00:30:39,640
His calligraphy is very valuable.

597
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:41,070
Yes, the real ones are valuable.

598
00:30:41,070 --> 00:30:42,160
This one is a fake.

599
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:43,560
It's not worth anything.

600
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:46,070
I want this one.

601
00:30:47,590 --> 00:30:48,920
It's fake.

602
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:50,480
I like fakes.

603
00:30:51,790 --> 00:30:52,270
Okay?

604
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:55,030
Okay.

605
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,480
Well, tonight,

606
00:30:58,550 --> 00:30:59,400
I'll break your arm

607
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,790
at the entrance of the committee office.

608
00:31:00,790 --> 00:31:02,310
It takes a hundred days
to recover from a broken bone.

609
00:31:02,310 --> 00:31:03,680
At that point, who's going to force you

610
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:04,680
to transfer to the provincial capital?

611
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,640
Even with your arm in a sling,

612
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:06,590
you can still go to work.

613
00:31:06,590 --> 00:31:07,590
What do you think?

614
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,490
If you think it's suitable,

615
00:31:09,750 --> 00:31:11,810
I definitely have no problem with it.

616
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,330
Bro,

617
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:26,160
the big truck is trying to overtake us.

618
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:27,110
If I let him overtake us,

619
00:31:27,110 --> 00:31:29,110
I'll change my name to Fang Beichao.

620
00:31:32,870 --> 00:31:35,820
♪ Stars are twinkling over Crescent Bay ♪

621
00:31:39,820 --> 00:31:44,440
♪ A gentle breeze
sways the willow branches ♪

622
00:31:42,830 --> 00:31:44,230
Bro, you're impressive.

623
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:50,300
♪ A gentle breeze
sways the willow branches ♪

624
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:49,760
Bro,

625
00:31:49,790 --> 00:31:51,520
the big truck has overtaken us.

626
00:31:54,030 --> 00:31:57,110
♪ Sneaking around, peeking through ♪

627
00:31:54,130 --> 00:31:55,660
Overtaken Fang, chase him!

628
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:58,600
Chase him.

629
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,030
Okay.

630
00:32:16,830 --> 00:32:17,890
What's wrong, bro?

631
00:32:31,590 --> 00:32:31,830
Bro,

632
00:32:31,830 --> 00:32:33,880
right now I just want to go up and ram it.

633
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:35,090
That's a truck.

634
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:35,680
If we ram it,

635
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:37,340
that would be a fatal mistake.

636
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,740
Bro, you're right.

637
00:32:39,030 --> 00:32:40,160
Our "tool" really

638
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:41,910
does need upgrading.

639
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:42,750
I did say

640
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:44,720
that sharpening the axe
won't delay chopping wood.

641
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,000
But now it won't start.

642
00:32:46,030 --> 00:32:48,230
Are we going to carry it to get upgraded?

643
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:51,590
Snow covers the Volga River.

644
00:32:52,030 --> 00:32:54,160
Troikas run on the frozen river.

645
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,200
Troikas.

646
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:27,160
Weren't you driving pretty fast?

647
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,270
Why did you stop here?

648
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:29,200
Come on, chase me!

649
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:29,720
Come on!

650
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:30,310
Come on!

651
00:33:30,310 --> 00:33:31,000
Come on, get out.

652
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:31,590
Get out.

653
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:33,710
You...

654
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:42,920
Bro,

655
00:33:44,350 --> 00:33:45,740
you need a tire repair.

656
00:33:46,270 --> 00:33:47,460
It's cheap here.

657
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,070
Mao.

658
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:53,880
Mao.

659
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:57,960
Mao!

660
00:34:07,750 --> 00:34:11,630
[No swimming.]

661
00:34:13,150 --> 00:34:13,840
Back then,

662
00:34:16,590 --> 00:34:18,520
when I first came from the village,

663
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:22,560
I had no education and no skills,

664
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,530
and couldn't find any work.

665
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:29,570
I was about to starve.

666
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:32,739
It was you, Mao,

667
00:34:34,030 --> 00:34:35,360
and Gang who took me in.

668
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:44,210
Coming here means stability.

669
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:46,060
[Xia Tinggang, Thief]

670
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,760
I'll give you 3,500 yuan a month.

671
00:34:47,020 --> 00:34:47,929
[Mao Hongwei, Thief]

672
00:34:50,150 --> 00:34:50,590
Right.

673
00:34:51,110 --> 00:34:53,040
And food and lodging are included.

674
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,280
Gang, Mao,

675
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,960
whatever works. You decide.

676
00:34:58,230 --> 00:34:58,880
This Gai...

677
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:00,350
Little Gai is good.

678
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,740
Not only did you take me in,

679
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:06,480
but you also taught me

680
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:09,290
the rules of survival in this city.

681
00:35:10,850 --> 00:35:11,250
What?

682
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:13,070
-Where should we go to
grab a bite and have a drink?
-Bro, let's get some barbecue.

683
00:35:13,070 --> 00:35:14,270
-Bro.
-“Have a drink.

684
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:15,070
Wait, why...

685
00:35:15,110 --> 00:35:16,370
Why is it only 400 yuan?

686
00:35:17,110 --> 00:35:18,000
Wasn't it 3,500 yuan?

687
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,030
Wait, you eat my food
and sleep in my place.

688
00:35:19,030 --> 00:35:20,090
It all costs money.

689
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:21,560
Wait, bro.

690
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:23,430
I did all the work myself.

691
00:35:25,190 --> 00:35:27,120
Do you even have a conscience, Gai?

692
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,360
Do you know

693
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:30,420
what gratitude is?

694
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,220
If it weren't for you guys,

695
00:35:34,510 --> 00:35:35,440
I wouldn't have gone down

696
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,630
the path I'm on now.

697
00:35:44,030 --> 00:35:44,590
Gai,

698
00:35:47,710 --> 00:35:49,230
spare me, please.

699
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:51,400
Mao,

700
00:35:52,510 --> 00:35:54,040
what are you talking about?

701
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:57,060
I'm showing my gratitude.

702
00:36:00,710 --> 00:36:01,630
But let's

703
00:36:01,670 --> 00:36:03,530
put our personal feelings aside.

704
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:06,780
You punctured our company's car;

705
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,440
you still have to pay for it.

706
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:09,040
Of course,

707
00:36:09,190 --> 00:36:09,790
I will pay.

708
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:10,600
100,000 yuan.

709
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:11,670
How much?

710
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:12,480
Too much?

711
00:36:14,110 --> 00:36:14,770
Just right.

712
00:36:17,990 --> 00:36:19,430
100,000 yuan?

713
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:21,070
100,000 yuan, you...

714
00:36:22,190 --> 00:36:22,840
Gai.

715
00:36:23,630 --> 00:36:24,320
Lord Gai!

716
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:26,700
I'm really begging you.

717
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:27,440
Forget 100,000 yuan.

718
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:28,230
I don't even have 500 yuan

719
00:36:28,230 --> 00:36:29,700
on me.

720
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,280
It's not that I don't want to
pay my respects to you.

721
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:32,740
This...

722
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:34,550
Even if I go out to borrow,

723
00:36:34,550 --> 00:36:36,150
no one will lend me any money.

724
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,010
Lord Gai.

725
00:36:37,710 --> 00:36:38,190
Mao,

726
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:39,810
don't be afraid,

727
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:41,800
I'm here.

728
00:36:43,970 --> 00:36:47,110
[IOU] [Borrower: Mao Hongwei]

729
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:52,310
[Yang Wei—private money lender]

730
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:06,340
[IOU] [Borrower: Mao Hongwei]

731
00:37:06,710 --> 00:37:07,230
Mao.

732
00:37:17,790 --> 00:37:19,350
[IOU] [Borrower: Mao Hongwei]

733
00:37:33,640 --> 00:37:34,700
The money is yours.

734
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,000
You paid me back.

735
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:47,960
Yours.

736
00:37:49,070 --> 00:37:50,480
What are you doing?

737
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:51,000
Take it.

738
00:37:52,590 --> 00:37:54,170
We agreed on this.

739
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:57,510
I thought you were joking.

740
00:37:57,510 --> 00:37:57,960
What are you doing?

741
00:37:57,960 --> 00:37:58,950
Take it back.

742
00:37:59,190 --> 00:37:59,590
Wait,

743
00:38:00,190 --> 00:38:01,790
why are you pushing it?

744
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:02,760
Looking down on me?

745
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:03,550
Stop pushing.

746
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:05,230
What are you doing? You...

747
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,280
Gai, if you're going to do this...

748
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:08,950
What?

749
00:38:10,230 --> 00:38:11,190
If you have any other friends
who need money,

750
00:38:11,190 --> 00:38:12,850
introduce them to me anytime.

751
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,930
I'll lend them whatever they need.

752
00:38:18,550 --> 00:38:20,150
Let's go. I'll give you a ride

753
00:38:20,190 --> 00:38:21,070
to get some help.

754
00:38:21,070 --> 00:38:21,910
That's great.

755
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:26,480
Mao,

756
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:29,420
we haven't seen each other for years.

757
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:31,320
I don't really have

758
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:32,780
anything good to give you.

759
00:38:34,230 --> 00:38:35,090
Just a stack...

760
00:38:36,110 --> 00:38:36,800
Take this.

761
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:39,440
I've had this with me for a few days.

762
00:38:39,440 --> 00:38:40,800
I've grown attached to it.

763
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:41,460
You take it.

764
00:38:41,950 --> 00:38:42,480
Take it.

765
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:45,890
Take care of yourself.

766
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,050
Th-Thank you.
